whole_object: Looks like those people are about to embark on a 'fare-ly' interesting journey – they're getting a crash course in street-crossing while hitching a ride on the giggle express!
single_object:
- Bus: When the bus goes on a "see-food" diet, it devours the whole city in one tour!
- People: Pedestrians have their own social network; it's called the sidewalk, and they're constantly updating their "current location."
- Buildings: The buildings are having a competition to see who can stretch out of bed the tallest in the morning skyline.
- Crosswalk: The crosswalk is the city's barcode, and every pedestrian is a unique product passing through.
- Cars: Every car is a rolling karaoke box, but the world's worst singers always seem to have their windows down!
- Trash bags: The sidewalk's version of a black-tie event includes trash bags wearing their sleekest, shiniest plastic.
- Street signs: The street signs are the city's oldest teachers, but they only ever teach one lesson: "Read me or else!"

multi_object_dict.object_sentence: The bus is so big, it needs its own crosswalk just to let the people know it’s on a sightseeing tour of the city’s best traffic jams!
The people are dodging the trash bags like they’re in an Olympic event, proving that avoiding garbage is a true art form!
The buildings are so tall, they’re giving the cars a complex about their height—talk about a skyscraper complex!
The crosswalk is like a dance floor, but the street signs keep changing the music, making everyone do the cha-cha instead of the walk!
The cars are honking at the bus, but it’s just trying to take a leisurely stroll down the street—who knew buses could be so laid-back?
The trash bags are plotting to take over the buildings, claiming they have more character than some of the tenants!
The street signs are giving directions, but the people are just following their hearts—clearly, GPS isn’t the only navigation system!
